records.addlTxt: 2:31 PM Defendant Jinai Chontal Jaqushua Broomfield in court.  Attorney Faun Michelle Moses in court for Jinai Chontal Jaqushua Broomfield.  Prosecuting attorney Gerald Anthony Urbik in court for the State of Wisconsin. Amended information filed copy to defendant reading waived. Count 1 defendant pleads guilty. Court withholds finding of guilt and holds open count 1. Counts 2, 3 and 4 defendant pleads no contest. Court finds defendant guilty of counts 2, 3 and 4. Court orders 12 months probation, any treatment deemed necessary and costs due within 60 days. Defendant may petition to dismiss count 1 upon successful completion of probation. Sentence credit 2 days.
